caption:
Table 1: Evaluation results of semantic segmentation by adapting from GTAV to Cityscapes. The mechanism "T", "A", and "S" 
mean image translation, adversarial training, and self-supervised learning, respectively. The best results are highlighted in 
bold.

Table 2: Evaluation results of semantic segmentation by adapting from SYNTHIA to Cityscapes. The mechanism "T", "A", and 
"S" mean image translation, adversarial learning, and self-supervised learning, respectively. We show the mIoU (%) of the 13 
classes (mIoU*) excluding classes with "*". "-" represents the method does not report the corresponding experimental result. 
The best results are highlighted in bold.

Table 3: Ablation study of the proposed method in terms of 
mIoU (%) on the two tasks. Here, "Baseline" represents the 
original adversarial learning without entropy reweighting.

Table 4: Parameter analysis of the weighting factor for the 
entropy reweighting adversarial loss in terms of mIoU (%).

Table 5: Comparison of the proposed UASL and standard 
self-supervised learning method with different thresholds 
in terms of mIoU (%).
